            <p><strong><span>WHAT ARE NEUTRAL COLORS? HOW TO WEAR THEM? </span></strong></p>
            <p><span>Neutral colors are calming and relaxing to the eye &amp; include shades of black, white, ivory, cream, and grey. </span></p>
            <p><span>Colors like Orange &amp; purple, though being bright colors are somewhat gender-fluid too, as they do not define their attribution to a particular gender. </span></p>
            <p><span>The beauty of wearing neutrals is that they all pair together. Instead of competing with each other, you can simply pair any of the two-three pieces together. That&rsquo;s why it&rsquo;s imperative to have at least some Gender-neutral pieces, that way you can make the most of your closet.</span></p>
            <p><span>Some colors have neutral-like characteristics, such as earth tones like sage and olive greens, burnt orange, sand, and shades of blue including navy and denim. You can also consider pale blush a neutral color because of my light skin tone.&nbsp; </span></p>
